name: Nokia 7 Plus
description: The Nokia 7 Plus is the first smartphone from the company to sport an 18:9 display. It has a 6-inch IPS display with Corning Gorilla Glass for protection. Powering the phone is a Snapdragon 660 processor with 4GB of RAM and 64GB of internal storage.

name: OnePlus TV
description: The OnePlus TV has a 55-inch QLED display and Dolby Vision support. The Android TV will receive software updates for at least three years. It has eight speakers with 50W output combined, Dolby Atmos support, and a custom Gamma Color Magic processor. OnePlus TV Q1 Pro features a QLED 55-inch panel with 4K resolution

name: Dell Inspiron 15 5000
description: Dell Inspiron 15 5000 is a Windows 10 laptop with a 15.60-inch display that has a resolution of 1920x1080 pixels. It is powered by a Core i5 processor and it comes with 8GB of RAM. The Dell Inspiron 15 5000 packs 256GB of HDD storage. Graphics are powered by AMD Radeon 530 Graphics.

name: Samsung Galaxy Note 10
description: Samsung Galaxy Note 10 is powered by a 1.9GHz octa-core Samsung Exynos 9825 processor that features 4 cores clocked at 1.9GHz, 2 cores clocked at 2.4GHz and 2 cores clocked at 2.7GHz.
